<p>In my ViewController I have an empty UIImageVIew that I am hoping to populate with an image.</p>  <p>The user taps a button, a modal view pops up and the user draws an image.</p>  <p>Then the user taps 'Done' which fires an unwind segue back to my view controller.</p>  <p>In that unwind segue function I am attempting to update the UIImage to no avail.</p>  <p>I am definitely getting an image back through though, I just don't think its updating the UIImageView.</p>  <p>This is the Unwind Segue function in my main view controller:</p>  <pre><code>@IBAction func saveImage(segue:UIStoryboardSegue) {      println("Should be able to save here right?")     if(segue.sourceViewController .isKindOfClass(CustomerFairProcessingSignatureViewController))     {         var view2:ModalViewController = segue.sourceViewController as! ModalViewController            if view2.imageView.image != nil{             //img is an IBOutlet           img.image = view2.imageView.image          }else{           println("Theres no image brah")         }       } } </code></pre>